Download Desktop Docker & Node JS
----------------------------------

> open Docker QuickStart Terminal (allow all the messages)
> Inside the Docker QuickStart Terminal --> docker --version


Open VS Code:-
----------------
> add extension of Docker(Microsoft)
> create a folder(dock)
> create a file(dockerfile) in folder 

> create a JS file as file_name.js --> console.log("Name: Your_nmae");
                                       console.log("Class: TE");
                                       console.log("Subject: LP - II Web Application Development");
                                       console.log("Assignment-4b");
                           (SAVE)
                           

> open Docker file --> FROM node:alpine
                       COPY . /folder_name
                       CMD node /folder_name/file_name.js
                      
                        (SAVE)                         


Open VS Code Terminal:-
-------------------------
> cd folder_name
> docker --version
> node file_name.js
> docker build -t folder_name .
> docker images
